-- Government 10-Year Bond Decline in India Before Tomorrow's Debt Auction
-- V Ramakrishnan
-- 2010-07-08T03:46:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/government-10-year-bond-decline-in-india-before-tomorrow-s-debt-auction.html

          
          
             India’s 10-year bonds dropped,
snapping a two-day advance, before the sale of 120 billion
rupees ($2.6 billion) of debt tomorrow. The yield on the 7.8
percent note due May 2020 rose two basis point to 7.59 percent
as of 9:08 a.m. in Mumbai, according to the central bank’s
trading system.  
